# Cursor Rules — Goodwin Bricklaying
# BrightPath Creative | goodwinbricklaying.com.au
# These rules apply to every file, component, and decision in this project.

## Project Identity
You are building a premium, image-led website for Goodwin Bricklaying — a luxury masonry specialist
in Melbourne, Australia. The site must feel like a high-end architecture studio, not a trades website.
Read docs/brief.md and docs/content-notes.md before generating any code.

## Non-Negotiable Design Rules
- Use ONLY the colour palette defined in docs/content-notes.md — no exceptions
- Font weights: 300–400 only. Never bold (700+)
- Generous negative space — never crowd elements
- All images must have descriptive, keyword-rich alt text (see docs/seo.md for conventions)
- Apply warm image treatment: filter: sepia(0.12) saturate(0.92) brightness(0.96)
- Hero overlays: rgba(78, 67, 61, 0.72)
- Buttons: outlined only, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.2em, never rounded

## Copy Rules
- Never use: "affordable", "cheap", "competitive rates", "free quote", "no job too big or small"
- Never claim David is a licensed builder — he is NOT
- All copy is approved and final — use it verbatim from docs/copy/*.md
- Do not paraphrase or rewrite copy unless explicitly asked

## Technical Standards (2025/2026)
- Semantic HTML5: use <header>, <nav>, <main>, <article>, <section>, <footer> correctly
- One <h1> per page only
- Every page needs: unique <title>, meta description, canonical tag, Open Graph tags
- Images: WebP format, lazy-loaded (except hero), explicit width and height attributes
- Hero video/media: autoplay, muted, loop, playsinline, preload="none"
- Include skip link at top of every page: <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
- Breadcrumbs on all inner pages with BreadcrumbList schema
- All forms submit to BrightPath CRM (GoHighLevel) — wire to endpoint when provided
- robots.txt at domain root pointing to sitemap.xml
- sitemap.xml listing all canonical URLs
- llms.txt at domain root (already created — do not modify)
- Privacy Policy, Cookie Policy pages must exist before launch

## SEO & Schema
- FAQPage schema on every page that has FAQ content
- LocalBusiness + HomeAndConstructionBusiness schema on homepage
- BreadcrumbList schema on all inner pages
- Open Graph tags on every page (og:title, og:description, og:image, og:url, og:type)
- All URLs: lowercase, hyphen-separated, no query strings
- 301 redirect: goodwinbrickblockandheritage.com.au → goodwinbricklaying.com.au

## AEO / LLM Optimisation
- FAQ sections must use proper <details>/<summary> or structured HTML — not hidden content
- Self-contained answer paragraphs — each FAQ answer must make sense without surrounding context
- Structured data (JSON-LD) in <head> of every page
- llms.txt is in the project root — ensure it is served at /llms.txt

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Minimum contrast ratio 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- All interactive elements keyboard-accessible with visible focus states
- ARIA roles on complex/dynamic components
- Skip link visible on keyboard focus at top of page
- All form inputs have associated <label> elements

## File & Asset Conventions
- Images: /public/images/[service]-[description]-[suburb]-[number].webp
- Logo: /public/logo/goodwin-logo.svg (white version); goodwin-logo-grey-brown.svg (dark version); goodwin-logo-seo.png (raster for SEO schema)
- Never recreate or alter the logo in code — use the SVG asset only
- Placeholder images: earthy brown solid (#5B4F47) until real photography supplied

## Placeholders in Copy
- [CRM Number] → replace with CRM tracking number (to be supplied)
- [BUTTON] → styled CTA button per design spec
- [PHONE] → click-to-call link using CRM number

## What to Build First
1. Global layout: nav, footer, colour tokens, typography
2. Homepage
3. Service pages (5)
4. About page
5. Contact page
6. Location pages (9)
7. Testimonials page
8. 404 page
9. Privacy Policy + Cookie Policy
10. robots.txt, sitemap.xml (auto-generate if possible)
